<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10468765>
    dc:description "FIGURES 33–48. 33–36. Roddenberryus sargi (F. O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1899). 37–40. R. spock Sánchez-Ruiz & Bonaldo, 2023. 41–48. Nops campeche Sánchez-Ruiz & Brescovit, 2018 (41–44, male; 45–48, female). 33, 37, 41, 45. Habitus, dorsal; 34, 38, 46, 47. Sternum, ventral; 35, 39. Tuberculate area and slits on anterior plate of genitalia (arrow point slits), dorsal. 36, 40, 48. Internal genitalia, digested and cleared (black arrow point tuberculate area. 42. Male palp, prolateral; 43. Same, apical; 44. Same, retrolateral. Scale bars 33–34, 37–38, 41, 45–47: 1.00 mm; 36, 40, 42–44: 0.50 mm; 48: 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: ap, anterior plate; arb, anteromedian receptacle base; Cb, cymbium; cs, chemosensory setae patch; e, embolus; ete, embolar tip extensions; lo, lobes on posterior receptaculum; pp, posterior plate; pr, posterior receptacle; Ti, tibia; ue, uterus externus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10468765/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

